  OmniCare Clinical Copilot — Progress Brief for HPM Awards
     
  The Journey: Prototype → Production Architecture
     
  ---
  Where We Started

  The initial prototype was a research-grade Colab notebook — five notebooks chained together, running on a borrowed T4 GPU, with models loaded directly into Colab memory. A 
  custom Python agent framework (utils/agents.py) orchestrated 5 clinical agents, but it was tightly coupled, not deployable, and would collapse the moment the Colab session 
  ended. Data persisted to Firestore and the Healthcare API, which were the only production-grade elements. There was no API, no frontend contract, no path to real clinical
  use.

  ---
  What Changed: Criterion by Criterion

  1. Impact

  Before: Demo only — worked inside a Colab notebook
  Now: Deployable system a real clinic could point audio at
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Before: One developer could run it at a time
  Now: Multi-user sessions via Vertex AI Agent Engine
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Before: Transcript + SOAP only
  Now: Full pipeline: Audio → Transcription + HeAR respiratory detection → SOAP note, with Phase 2 roadmap for vitals, radiology, and discharge summary

  The architecture is now designed around a real clinical workflow — not a demo. The separation of frontend/backend with a clean API means a clinical team can actually use   
  this without touching code.

  2. Implementation

  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                     Before                     │                              Now                              │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Colab notebooks — not deployable               │ Vertex AI Agent Engine + Cloud Run proxy — managed, always-on │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Models loaded into Colab RAM (lost on timeout) │ RunPod serverless GPU endpoints — persistent, dedicated       │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Custom ad-hoc agent framework                  │ Google ADK (SequentialAgent pipeline, session.state handoffs) │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ No API surface                                 │ Clean REST + SSE contract for frontend integration            │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Binary audio in API body (not viable)          │ GCS signed URLs — audio uploaded directly to cloud storage    │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  The switch from a notebook to ADK + Agent Engine is the biggest structural leap. The system now has a defined entry point, a defined data contract, and a defined path to   
  production.

  3. Scalability

  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  
  │                        Before                        │                                                       Now                                                       │  
  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  
  │ One Colab GPU — zero concurrency                     │ RunPod serverless scales horizontally per request                                                               │  
  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  
  │ All models in one process                            │ Three isolated endpoints (Whisper, HeAR, MedGemma) — scale independently                                        │  
  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  
  │ Adding a new clinical agent meant editing a monolith │ New agent = one file in agents/, one file in tools/, one line in sub_agents                                     │  
  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  
  │ No phase 2 path                                      │ Phase 2 expansion designed in: VitalsMonitorAgent, RadiologyAgent, DischargeAgent slot in without restructuring │  
  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  

  The SequentialAgent pipeline pattern means the system grows by addition, not by rewriting.

  4. Innovation

  Before: HeAR integrated but as a standalone notebook cell
  Now: HeAR runs as a dedicated agent in the pipeline — events feed directly into SOAP generation
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Before: MedGemma quantized on a consumer GPU
  Now: MedGemma 1.5 4B-IT on a dedicated vLLM endpoint — consistent latency, no cold-start quality loss
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Before: Three models running in sequence by hand
  Now: Multi-agent orchestration — each model has a purpose, a defined input/output contract, and logs to Firestore for auditability
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Before: Google Cloud used for storage only
  Now: Google ADK + Vertex AI Agent Engine + Healthcare API + Firestore — full Google Cloud medical AI stack

  The combination of HeAR (acoustic respiratory detection) + Whisper (speech) + MedGemma (medical reasoning) in a single orchestrated pipeline remains the differentiating
  technical bet. No other system in this space is using all three together in real-time.

  ---
  One-Paragraph Summary for Judges

  OmniCare Clinical Copilot has moved from a proof-of-concept running inside a Google Colab notebook to a fully specified production MVP architecture. The core pipeline —
  Audio → Whisper transcription + HeAR respiratory event detection → MedGemma SOAP note — is unchanged in intent, but every layer underneath it has been replaced. Models now
  run on dedicated RunPod serverless GPU endpoints, orchestration is handled by Google's Agent Development Kit on Vertex AI Agent Engine, and a clean REST + SSE API separates
  frontend from backend for parallel team development. The system is designed to grow: Phase 2 agents for vitals monitoring, radiology, and discharge summaries slot in without
  restructuring. The architecture is now something a real clinic could deploy — not just something a researcher could demo.


