  ── RESPIRATORY / HeAR IMPACT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

  The HeAR layer is OmniCare's clinical differentiator beyond documentation.

  The Problem
  ───────────
  • 550 million people globally live with chronic respiratory disease (WHO)
  • COPD and asthma exacerbations are among the most common reasons for unplanned hospitalization
  • Average cost of a COPD hospitalization: $20,000–$35,000 (US)
  • Most exacerbations are preceded by acoustic changes (cough pattern, wheeze) days before symptoms
    worsen — but clinicians cannot monitor every patient continuously

  OmniCare's HeAR Value
  ──────────────────────
  • HeAR detects cough and respiratory events during consultations that are inaudible or overlooked
  • Clinical suggestion is generated immediately: "Early wheeze pattern detected — consider
    spirometry follow-up"
  • Catching 1 COPD hospitalization per 50 high-risk patients: saves ~$20,000–35,000 per event
  • At 2,000 physicians, each with 5 high-risk respiratory patients: 10,000 patients monitored
    → 200 hospitalizations potentially avoided → $4M–$7M in healthcare cost avoidance/year

  AI Cough Monitoring Market validation: $6B in the US alone (2024), growing to $10.7B by 2032.
  OmniCare integrates this into a general clinical workflow — no standalone app needed.

